---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="About the author behind this site.">
  <section class="page-head section">
    <p class="eyebrow">About</p>

    <div class="about-intro">
      <div>
        <h1>
          <span>Software Engineer</span>
        </h1>

        <p class="lead">
          Hi, I'm Karan! I'm a software engineer from London with a strong
          interest in scalable and reliable systems, reading, AI safety and
          Effective Altruism.
        </p>

        <p class="lead">
          I'm building <a href="https://epilogue.club/">Epilogue Club</a>, a
          book discovery platform that helps you find your next book.
        </p>

        <p class="lead">
          Outside of work, I enjoy reading, playing board games, exploring new
          restaurants in London, disconnecting from technology and meeting
          driven but extremely kind people in the Effective Altruism community
          (if you're also kind and driven, but not in the EA community, I would
          enjoy meeting you, too!).
        </p>
      </div>

      <img
        class="about-portrait"
        src="/media/leela-leaning-back-pre-welcome.png"
      />
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section prose-grid">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">Interests</p>
      <h2>Reading + Effective Altruism.</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="prose-stack">
      <b class="lead">Reading:</b>
      <p class="lead">
        I tend to like thought-provoking non-fiction books, usually accessible
        science books and biographies/memoirs. Here are some of my favourites
        broken down by genre:

        <ul class="lead">
          <li>All-time favourite: all seven Harry Potter books</li>
          <li>Science: 'Why We Sleep', Matthew Walker</li>
          <li>Sociology: 'The Better Angels of our Nature', Steven Pinker</li>
          <li>History: 'Homo Deus', Yuval Noah Harari</li>
          <li>Fantasy: Stardust, Neil Gaiman</li>
          <li>Memoir: Educated, Tara Westover</li>
        </ul>
      </p>

      <b class="lead">Effective Altruism:</b>
      <p class="lead">
        The main cause areas I'm interested in are:
        <ul class="lead">
          <li>AI safety</li>
          <li>Global health and development</li>
          <li>Earning to give</li>
          <li>Climate change</li>
        </ul>
      </p>

      <p>In case you’re wondering, yes, I like bullet points.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

